cff-version: 1.2.0
message: "If you use this repository, please cite it as below."
title: "A Functional Taxonomy of the Web of Agents: Operational Definitions and an Empirical Validation Protocol"
abstract: >-
  The Web of Agents has cycled through three architectural
  generations (FIPA/BDI multi-agent systems, the Semantic Web,
  LLM-powered agents) with markedly different adoption outcomes.
  This repository accompanies an article that contributes a four-axis
  functional taxonomy, an operational codebook with measurable
  criteria for each axis value, a pre-registered three-part
  validation protocol (inter-rater reliability, predictive validity,
  LLM-as-classifier), and a three-rater LLM-self-consistency pilot
  on five exemplar systems. All rater outputs and a reproducibility
  script are included.
type: software
